      <p>Ongoing inquiries, experiments, and reading trails. These are living questions rather than polished answers.</p>
    </header>

    <section class="project-list wrap">
      <article class="project"><span class="project-num">01</span><div><h2>Visual explanations for AI systems</h2><p>How might spatial notes, diagrams, and progressive disclosure help technical readers reason about model behaviour?</p></div><span class="project-type">Active · Human-AI</span><span>↗</span></article>
      <article class="project"><span class="project-num">02</span><div><h2>High Performance Computing for AI</h2><p>Understanding how systems choices, memory movement, kernels, and parallelism shape the speed of model inference.</p></div><span class="project-type">Reading trail · HPC</span><span>↗</span></article>
      <article class="project"><span class="project-num">03</span><div><h2>Interfaces as learning environments</h2><p>Exploring how explanations and tooling can teach mental models without turning into instruction manuals.</p></div><span class="project-type">Writing · Design</span><span>↗</span></article>
